org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.asn1.coer

Class COERBitString

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.asn1.coer.COERBitString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, COEREncodable, Encodable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EndEntityType

    public class COERBitString
extends java.lang.Object
implements COEREncodable
    COER Encoding of a bit string.

    For more information see ISO/IEC 8825-7:2015 Section 13

    Important: a maximum bitstring of 64 bits are supported.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • COERBitString

        public COERBitString(long bitString,
                     java.lang.Integer length,
                     boolean fixedSize)
              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Constructor used when encoding a bit string.

        If setFlag methods should be used, set bitString to 0 initially and call setFlag for each position.

        Parameters:
        bitString - the value of the string.
        length - the length of the string.
        fixedSize - if the size of the string is fixed or variable.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if length was invalid.
